Later on, all Zenke shrines except for {{ill|Ukishima Shrine and Yomochi Shrine#Ukishima Shrine|ja|世持神社|lt=Choju Shrine|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Choraku-ji Tenmangū|en}} would convert to {{ill|Shingon Buddhism|ja|真言宗|12=draft|12=draft}} and become the {{ill|Eight Ryukyu Shrines|en}}.


.

Excluded from this list is {{ill|Kin-gū|en|12=draft|12=draft}}


, which, although quite small, was always affiliated with the {{ill|Shingon Buddhist|ja|真言宗|12=draft|12=draft}} temple {{ill|Kin Kannon-ji|en}},


 and also joined the {{ill|Eight Ryukyu Shrines|en|12=draft|12=draft}}


.

